step.reason:
%text
Distance covered by $M_A$ running at $S_A$ to
reach the meeting 7 hr away is $7S_A$. Distance
covered by $M_B$ to reach the same meeting
is $7S_B$.
But $M_A$ running at $(S_A-1)$ km/h took two
hours longer in getting back than $M_B$ running
at $(S_B+1)$ km/h did. Putting this in equation
form,
%
\begin{align}
  &\overbrace{\dfrac{7S_A}{S_A-1}(hr)}^\text{$M_A$ return time}
  -\overbrace{\dfrac{7S_B}{S_B+1}(hr)}^\text{$M_B$ return time}
  =\overbrace{2(hr)}^\text{time difference} 
\end{align}
